                <figure class="infographic-frame">
                    <img src="/infographics/cii-qualification-levels-comparison-infographic.svg" alt="Infographic comparing RQF qualification levels across the CII Certificate, Diploma, and Advanced Diploma in Insurance." loading="lazy" />
                    <figcaption class="infographic-caption">Each CII qualification tier increases in credit value, assessment complexity, and knowledge depth — from 15-credit MCQ units at Level 3 through to 50-credit research submissions at Level 7.</figcaption>
                </figure>

                <p class="intro">The CII Certificate in Insurance at RQF Level 3 is the direct entry point to the <a href="/CII-Diploma-in-Insurance">CII Diploma in Insurance</a> at RQF Level 4 and Level 6. Certificate credits can contribute toward Diploma credit requirements. The progression represents a significant shift in assessment format: Certificate units use MCQ scenario-based computer exams worth 15 credits each, while Diploma units use written examinations worth 20–30 credits per unit.</p>

